Use these rules for **borrower_pro (Demo_Client)** — the borrower-facing frontend for TrueKredit Pro. Borrowers register and borrow money online (digital license KPKT).

---

## 1) Context

- **Host app (this folder)**: `apps/borrower_pro/Demo_Client/` — Next.js app shell: routes, env, Better Auth API route, proxy, branding, `globals.css`, `lib/version.ts`, and server-only helpers (`lib/auth-server.ts`, `lib/borrower-auth-server.ts`).
- **Shared package (sibling folders)**: `apps/borrower_pro/components/` and `apps/borrower_pro/lib/` — all reusable UI, clients, validation, and onboarding. Import via `@borrower_pro/...` (see `Demo_Client/tsconfig.json` paths). **Do not duplicate** shared code into Demo_Client; add features under `../components` or `../lib` instead.
- **Backend**: `backend_pro` — Better Auth, borrower APIs.

---

## 2) Framework & Structure

- **Next.js 16.x** with App Router.
- TypeScript only.
- Organize by feature: `app/(auth)/sign-in`, `app/(auth)/sign-up`, `app/(dashboard)/`, etc.
- Next.js 16 uses `proxy.ts` instead of middleware files.

---

## 3) Shared code (maximum reuse)

| Location | Contents |
|----------|----------|
| `apps/borrower_pro/components/` | ShadCN `ui/`, feature components (forms, loan center, **ThemeProvider**, **onboarding wizard**), etc. |
| `apps/borrower_pro/lib/` | Auth/loan/application clients, form types/validation, **`onboarding-storage-keys.ts`** (localStorage key names for onboarding draft/dismiss). |

- Demo_Client pages should import: `@borrower_pro/components/...`, `@borrower_pro/lib/...`.
- **Theme**: `ThemeProvider` from `@borrower_pro/components/theme-provider`. Each host may pass its own `storageKey` (e.g. `demo-client-theme` in `app/layout.tsx`).
- **Onboarding**: `OnboardingWizard` from `@borrower_pro/components/onboarding`. Use `ONBOARDING_DRAFT_KEY` / `ONBOARDING_DISMISSED_KEY` from `@borrower_pro/lib/onboarding-storage-keys` anywhere you read/write the same localStorage keys (e.g. dashboard banner, layout redirect).
- **Not shared** (stay in Demo_Client): Prisma-backed `auth-server.ts`, cookie-forwarding `borrower-auth-server.ts`, `app/api/proxy`, `lib/version.ts`.

---

## 4) Auth (Better Auth)

- Use **Better Auth** client for sign in / sign up (no admin plugin — borrower auth only).
- Session-based; cookies handled by Better Auth.
- Base URL = this app's URL (where auth API routes live). Auth routes at `app/api/auth/[...all]/route.ts`.

```typescript
// Example: createAuthClient for borrower (no adminClient)
import { createAuthClient } from "better-auth/react";

export const authClient = createAuthClient({
  baseURL: process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL || "http://localhost:3001",
});
```

Auth API route: `app/api/auth/[...all]/route.ts` using `toNextJsHandler` from Better Auth. Backend_pro verifies sessions; BETTER_AUTH_SECRET must match.

---

## 5) UI System

- Use **ShadCN UI** from shared `@borrower_pro/components/ui`.
- Use **sonner** for toasts.
- Refer to `docs/planning/brand.md` for Demo_Client branding (if present).

---

## 6) Theming & Typography

- Support light/dark theme (configurable per client via `ThemeProvider` + `storageKey`).
- Use fonts and colors from `brand.md` / `globals.css`.

### Colors — Do NOT Hardcode

**Never hardcode hex codes or Tailwind color names** (e.g. `#6151ca`, `red-500`, `emerald-500`, `amber-500`) in components.

- **Single source of truth**: HSL token values and the `hsl(var(--token))` mapping live in **`tailwind.config.ts`** (light/dark maps + `theme.extend` + `tailwindcss/plugin` injecting `:root` / `.dark`). **Do not** duplicate palette values in `app/globals.css`.
- **Use theme utilities**: `primary`, `success`, `warning`, `error`, `info` (e.g. `text-error`, `bg-success/10`, `border-primary`).
- See `docs/planning/brand.md` for the full color system (if present).

---

## 7) Forms & Validation

- Schema-based validation (Zod).
- Inline validation with consistent error messaging.
- Accessible, keyboard-friendly inputs.

---

## 8) Date, Time & Number Formatting

- Database: UTC. Frontend: display in Malaysia timezone (GMT+8).
- Use `formatDate`, `formatCurrency`, etc. from `@borrower_pro/lib/borrower-form-display` and related shared libs (not a duplicate `lib/utils` in the host for domain formatting).
- Use safe math utilities for any financial display.

---

## 9) Current scope

Borrower portal: auth, onboarding, applications, loans, profile, account, legal pages, etc.
